('proj-ai-product-teardown', 'ph-ai-foundations', 91, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional AI Product Teardown', 'Optional practice project: Analyze an existing AI product, map its model/API/data flow, identify failure modes, and propose measurable improvements.', 'side', 4, 'intermediate', '{"whatToBuild":"Analyze an existing AI product, map its model/API/data flow, identify failure modes, and propose measurable improvements.","buildSteps":["Define the AI Product Teardown scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: API behavior, model behavior and evaluation.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"proj-ai-product-teardown"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply AI Engineering Foundations through a focused AI Product Teardown artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The an working AI Product Teardown notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The AI Product Teardown scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('chk-ai-foundation-review', 'ph-ai-foundations', 99, 'checkpoint', 'assessment', NULL, NULL, 'AI Engineering Foundation Review', 'Review checkpoint for AI Engineering Foundations. The learner synthesizes completed topics such as What AI Engineers Build, AI vs ML Engineering vs Research, AI Product Discovery, Use Cases and Feasibility, records evidence, and updates the learning plan before continuing.', 'checkpoint', 2, 'intermediate', '{"reviewFocus":"Review checkpoint for AI Engineering Foundations. The learner synthesizes completed topics such as What AI Engineers Build, AI vs ML Engineering vs Research, AI Product Discovery, Use Cases and Feasibility, records evidence, and updates the learning plan before continuing.","reviewCriteria":["Write a concise review of the main ideas from this segment.","Include one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, lab output, code, query results, screenshots, or a project review.","Record open questions, weak areas, or follow-up actions.","Mark the checkpoint complete only after the review artifact and next steps are captured."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"chk-ai-foundation-review"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Explain how topics from AI Engineering Foundations connect to realistic AI engineering work.", "Select evidence that shows attempted practice, reasoning, or implementation decisions.", "Identify which topics need review before moving to later roadmap areas."]'::jsonb, '["Write a concise review of the main ideas from this segment.", "Include one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, lab output, code, query results, screenshots, or a project review.", "Record open questions, weak areas, or follow-up actions.", "Mark the checkpoint complete only after the review artifact and next steps are captured."]'::jsonb),
