('proj-data-analysis-notebook', 'ph-programming-math-data', 91, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional AI Dataset Analysis Notebook', 'Optional practice project: Analyze a messy text or tabular dataset, document assumptions, clean the data, and produce visual summaries.', 'side', 6, 'intermediate', '{"whatToBuild":"Analyze a messy text or tabular dataset, document assumptions, clean the data, and produce visual summaries.","buildSteps":["Define the AI Dataset Analysis Notebook scenario, target user or reviewer, and the specific Programming, Math, and Data Foundations concepts it will demonstrate.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"proj-data-analysis-notebook"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Programming, Math, and Data Foundations through a focused AI Dataset Analysis Notebook artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The an working AI Dataset Analysis Notebook notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The AI Dataset Analysis Notebook scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
