('proj-document-qa', 'ph-embeddings-rag', 91, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Document Q&A Bot', 'Optional practice project: Build a document Q&A app with chunking, embeddings, citations, and retrieval debugging.', 'side', 10, 'intermediate', '{"whatToBuild":"Build a document Q&A app with chunking, embeddings, citations, and retrieval debugging.","buildSteps":["Define the Document Q&A Bot scenario, target user or reviewer, and the specific Embeddings, Vector Search, and RAG concepts it will demonstrate.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"proj-document-qa"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Embeddings, Vector Search, and RAG through a focused Document Q&A Bot artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working Document Q&A Bot notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The Document Q&A Bot scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('ms-required-rag-app', 'ph-embeddings-rag', 92, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Production-Style RAG App', 'Capstone project: Build a RAG application with ingestion, vector search, citations, eval cases, and clear failure-mode documentation.', 'side', 16, 'intermediate', '{"whatToBuild":"Build a RAG application with ingestion, vector search, citations, eval cases, and clear failure-mode documentation.","buildSteps":["Define the Production-Style RAG App scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: retrieval and citations.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use.","Create a review checklist that connects the artifact to the relevant skills and roadmap segment.","Write a limitation and risk section so the project is presented as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim.","Document how to run or review the Production-Style RAG App deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"ms-required-rag-app"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Embeddings, Vector Search, and RAG through a focused Production-Style RAG App artifact.","Integrate multiple roadmap areas into one coherent case study rather than isolated exercises.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working Production-Style RAG App notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The Production-Style RAG App scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","The case study connects implementation decisions to relevant roadmap skills and explains why alternatives were not chosen.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness.","The project is packaged so a reviewer can understand the artifact without live mentoring."]'::jsonb),
('chk-rag-review', 'ph-embeddings-rag', 99, 'checkpoint', 'assessment', NULL, NULL, 'RAG System Review', 'Review checkpoint for Embeddings, Vector Search, and RAG. The learner synthesizes completed topics such as Embedding Model Selection, Semantic Similarity, Chunking Strategies, Metadata Design, records evidence, and updates the learning plan before continuing.', 'checkpoint', 2, 'intermediate', '{"reviewFocus":"Review checkpoint for Embeddings, Vector Search, and RAG. The learner synthesizes completed topics such as Embedding Model Selection, Semantic Similarity, Chunking Strategies, Metadata Design, records evidence, and updates the learning plan before continuing.","reviewCriteria":["Write a concise review of the main ideas from this segment.","Include one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, lab output, code, query results, screenshots, or a project review.","Record open questions, weak areas, or follow-up actions.","Mark the checkpoint complete only after the review artifact and next steps are captured."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"chk-rag-review"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Explain how topics from Embeddings, Vector Search, and RAG connect to realistic AI engineering work.", "Select evidence that shows attempted practice, reasoning, or implementation decisions.", "Identify which topics need review before moving to later roadmap areas."]'::jsonb, '["Write a concise review of the main ideas from this segment.", "Include one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, lab output, code, query results, screenshots, or a project review.", "Record open questions, weak areas, or follow-up actions.", "Mark the checkpoint complete only after the review artifact and next steps are captured."]'::jsonb),
