('proj-local-model-demo', 'ph-model-providers-open-source', 91, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Local Model Demo', 'Optional practice project: Run an open model locally or on a hosted server and compare quality, cost, latency, and operational tradeoffs.', 'side', 10, 'intermediate', '{"whatToBuild":"Run an open model locally or on a hosted server and compare quality, cost, latency, and operational tradeoffs.","buildSteps":["Define the Local Model Demo scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: model behavior and evaluation.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"proj-local-model-demo"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models through a focused Local Model Demo artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working Local Model Demo notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The Local Model Demo scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('chk-model-selection-review', 'ph-model-providers-open-source', 99, 'checkpoint', 'assessment', NULL, NULL, 'Model Selection Review', 'Review checkpoint for Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models. The learner synthesizes completed topics such as OpenAI Platform, Anthropic Claude, Google Gemini, Azure AI Foundry, records evidence, and updates the learning plan before continuing.', 'checkpoint', 2, 'intermediate', '{"reviewFocus":"Review checkpoint for Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models. The learner synthesizes completed topics such as OpenAI Platform, Anthropic Claude, Google Gemini, Azure AI Foundry, records evidence, and updates the learning plan before continuing.","reviewCriteria":["Write a concise review of the main ideas from this segment.","Include one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, lab output, code, query results, screenshots, or a project review.","Record open questions, weak areas, or follow-up actions.","Mark the checkpoint complete only after the review artifact and next steps are captured."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"chk-model-selection-review"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Explain how topics from Model APIs, Providers, and Open Source Models connect to realistic AI engineering work.", "Select evidence that shows attempted practice, reasoning, or implementation decisions.", "Identify which topics need review before moving to later roadmap areas."]'::jsonb, '["Write a concise review of the main ideas from this segment.", "Include one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, lab output, code, query results, screenshots, or a project review.", "Record open questions, weak areas, or follow-up actions.", "Mark the checkpoint complete only after the review artifact and next steps are captured."]'::jsonb),
