('proj-llmops-pipeline', 'ph-mlops-llmops', 91, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional LLMOps Pipeline', 'Optional practice project: Build a pipeline that ingests test cases, runs prompts against models, records traces, and blocks regressions.', 'side', 12, 'advanced', '{"whatToBuild":"Build a pipeline that ingests test cases, runs prompts against models, records traces, and blocks regressions.","buildSteps":["Define the LLMOps Pipeline scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: pipeline stages, test evidence.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"proj-llmops-pipeline"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply MLOps and LLMOps through a focused LLMOps Pipeline artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working LLMOps Pipeline notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The LLMOps Pipeline scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('chk-ops-readiness', 'ph-mlops-llmops', 99, 'checkpoint', 'assessment', NULL, NULL, 'MLOps and LLMOps Readiness Review', 'Review checkpoint for MLOps and LLMOps. The learner consolidates evidence from MLflow Tracking, Weights and Biases, Run Metadata, Artifact Logging, identifies unresolved prerequisite gaps, and decides whether to continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice before the next roadmap segment.', 'checkpoint', 2, 'advanced', '{"reviewFocus":"Review checkpoint for MLOps and LLMOps. The learner consolidates evidence from MLflow Tracking, Weights and Biases, Run Metadata, Artifact Logging, identifies unresolved prerequisite gaps, and decides whether to continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice before the next roadmap segment.","reviewCriteria":["List the roadmap items reviewed for this checkpoint.","Provide one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, a lab result, code, queries, screenshots, or a project review.","Record at least two gaps, risks, or follow-up actions, or explicitly state that no critical gaps were found.","Use the result to choose one next step: continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"chk-ops-readiness"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Summarize the main concepts and decisions from MLOps and LLMOps in practical AI engineering terms.", "Identify prerequisite gaps, unclear topics, or risks that should be reviewed before moving forward.", "Create a short evidence artifact that links completed roadmap items to what was learned."]'::jsonb, '["List the roadmap items reviewed for this checkpoint.", "Provide one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, a lab result, code, queries, screenshots, or a project review.", "Record at least two gaps, risks, or follow-up actions, or explicitly state that no critical gaps were found.", "Use the result to choose one next step: continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice."]'::jsonb),
