('proj-deploy-ai-api', 'ph-infra-deployment-observability', 91, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Deployed AI API', 'Optional practice project: Deploy an AI API with Docker, CI/CD, rate limits, logs, metrics, and a simple dashboard.', 'side', 12, 'advanced', '{"whatToBuild":"Deploy an AI API with Docker, CI/CD, rate limits, logs, metrics, and a simple dashboard.","buildSteps":["Define the Deployed AI API scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: API behavior, dashboard decisions, container setup, CI checks, deployment flow.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"proj-deploy-ai-api"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Observability through a focused Deployed AI API artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working Deployed AI API notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The Deployed AI API scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('ms-required-deployed-ai-system', 'ph-infra-deployment-observability', 92, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Deployed AI System', 'Capstone project: Deploy a production-style AI system with monitoring, tracing, cost controls, safety checks, and documented runbooks.', 'side', 18, 'advanced', '{"whatToBuild":"Deploy a production-style AI system with monitoring, tracing, cost controls, safety checks, and documented runbooks.","buildSteps":["Define the Deployed AI System scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: monitoring signals.","Choose the dataset, model, prompt, retrieval source, or tool boundary required by the project brief.","Build the baseline workflow first, then add the AI/ML behavior in a way that can be inspected.","Capture evaluation cases that include successful output, weak output, and at least one failure mode.","Add safeguards, citations, metrics, traces, or manual review notes where the project context requires them.","Document model assumptions, limitations, cost/latency concerns, and what would need review before real use.","Create a review checklist that connects the artifact to the relevant skills and roadmap segment.","Write a limitation and risk section so the project is presented as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim.","Document how to run or review the Deployed AI System deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"source":"roadmap.sh/ai-engineer","nodeKey":"ms-required-deployed-ai-system"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Observability through a focused Deployed AI System artifact.","Integrate multiple roadmap areas into one coherent case study rather than isolated exercises.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a working Deployed AI System notebook, service, or app with evaluation notes is available for review.","The Deployed AI System scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","The case study connects implementation decisions to relevant roadmap skills and explains why alternatives were not chosen.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness.","The project is packaged so a reviewer can understand the artifact without live mentoring."]'::jsonb),
